main event: A civilian reported seeing 18 to 20 objects drifting across the sky near Tyler, Texas in April 1966.
interesting points: The objects were described as having a sharp angle bend in their movement., The sighting occurred around 8:00 AM., The number of objects observed was 18 to 20., The report was forwarded to the Air Force by Mrs. Ellen Smith., The military conclusion classified the sighting as 'probable aircraft'.
witness description: A man and his wife observed the objects from their location.
